{"article_id":"RUWUDYArFfSyfKtD","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Story highlights","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"Obama says to Congress and all Americans :","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"watch the video of Syrian victims","depth":3},{"id":3,"text":"President Obama says","depth":3},{"id":4,"text":"time is needed","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"to consider Russian proposal","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"President Barack Obama tried Tuesday to sell a military intervention","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"he never wanted","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"to an American public","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"that opposes it ,","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"telling the nation","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"that he needed authorization","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"to attack Syria as leverage in a newly emerged diplomatic opening from Russia .","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"Calling the United States `` the anchor of global security , ''","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"Obama offered moral , political and strategic arguments","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"for being ready to launch limited military strikes","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"while trying to negotiate a diplomatic solution","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"to what he called Syria 's violation of a global ban on chemical weapons .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"`` Our ideals and principles , as well as our national security , are at stake in Syria , along with our leadership of a world","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"where we seek to ensure","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"that the worst weapons will never be used , ''","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"Obama said","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"in making the case","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"that the United States must act","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"when dictators such as Syrian President Bashar al-Assad `` brazenly '' violate international treaties","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"intended to protect humanity .","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"The 15-minute nationally televised speech initially was planned as Obama 's final push","depth":5},{"id":27,"text":"to win support from a skeptical public and Congress for his planned attack on Syria","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"for what his administration calls a major chemical weapons attack on August 21","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"that killed more than 1,400 people in suburban Damascus .","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"However , Monday 's unexpected diplomatic overture by Russia changed the strategic and political equation .","depth":5},{"id":31,"text":"Under the Russian plan ,","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"which still lacks any details ,","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"Syria would turn over its chemical weapons stockpiles to international control .","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"JUST WATCHED Kerry :","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"Obama 's priority is diplomacy","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"MUST WATCH Kerry :","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"Obama 's priority is diplomacy","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"02:11","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"JUST WATCHED Legislating a Syria solution","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"MUST WATCH Legislating a Syria solution 05:10","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"JUST WATCHED Russia 's diplomatic solution for Syria","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"MUST WATCH Russia 's diplomatic solution for Syria 03:10","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"How sarin gas affects the human body","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"MUST WATCH How sarin gas affects the human body 04:36","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"That would meet Obama 's main criterion","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"of ending the chemical weapons threat by the al-Assad regime .","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"However , Russia canceled a U.N. Security Council meeting","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"it had called for Tuesday","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"and rejected an initial proposal by France for the framework of a resolution ,","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"raising questions","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"about whether the diplomatic effort was serious or a stall tactic","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"to put off a U.S. attack on Syria .","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"For Obama , the Russian proposal","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"prompted by a seemingly off-the-cuff comment by U.S. Secretary of State John Kerry","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"further muddied an already complex challenge in Syria","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"compounded by public concerns of another possible military quagmire .","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"The president called the Russian offer an encouraging sign ,","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"but warned","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"that `` it 's too early","depth":14},{"id":65,"text":"to tell","depth":15},{"id":66,"text":"whether this offer will succeed ,","depth":15},{"id":67,"text":"and any agreement must verify","depth":14},{"id":68,"text":"that the Assad regime keeps its commitments . ''","depth":14},{"id":69,"text":"Therefore ,","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"he said ,","depth":13},{"id":71,"text":"he asked Congress to postpone a vote for now on authorizing military force against Syria .","depth":12},{"id":72,"text":"In addition , the diplomatic push will provide more time","depth":14},{"id":73,"text":"for United Nations inspectors to report their findings on the August attack","depth":14},{"id":74,"text":"and allow his administration to continue rallying support for an international response ,","depth":13},{"id":75,"text":"the president said .","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"At the same time ,","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"Obama said","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"he ordered the U.S. military to maintain its `` current posture","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"to keep the pressure on Assad","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"and to be in a position","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"to respond","depth":13},{"id":82,"text":"if diplomacy fails . ''","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"Kerry made the same argument at a congressional hearing Tuesday ,","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"telling legislators","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"that `` nothing focuses the mind like the prospect of a hanging . ''","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"However , congressional support for military action reflected public opposition .","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"A CNN/ORC International poll","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"released Monday","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"said","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"59 % of respondents opposed congressional authorization of military action ,","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"while 72 % said","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"American strikes would achieve no significant goals .","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"In an instant poll of people","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"who watched the speech Tuesday night ,","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"61 % favored Obama 's approach","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"compared to 37 %","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"who opposed it .","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"The CNN/ORC International survey showed","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"almost two-thirds of respondents thought","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"the Syria situation would be resolved through diplomatic efforts ,","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"while 47 % said","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"Obama made a convincing case for military action","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"compared to 50 %","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"who said","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"he did n't .","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"By CNN 's best estimate , the sample of poll respondents","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"-- 37 % Democrats , 20 % Republicans and 43 % independents --","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"was about seven percentage points more Democratic than the general public .","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"Critics call the situation","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"faced by Obama","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"his own doing for a confused Syria policy","depth":8},{"id":112,"text":"that he has never fully explained .","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"`` There 's a degree of incoherence","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"that I have never seen the likes of , ''","depth":8},{"id":115,"text":"veteran Republican Sen. John McCain of Arizona told CNN on Tuesday .","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"In the most emotional part of the speech , Obama cited the videos","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"his administration made public","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"that showed victims of the Syrian sarin gas attack .","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"`` The images from this massacre are sickening :","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"men , women , children","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"lying in rows ,","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"killed by poison gas ,","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"others","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"foaming at the mouth ,","depth":13},{"id":125,"text":"gasping for breath ,","depth":13},{"id":126,"text":"a father","depth":14},{"id":127,"text":"clutching his dead children ,","depth":14},{"id":128,"text":"imploring them to get up","depth":14},{"id":129,"text":"and walk , ''","depth":14},{"id":130,"text":"the president said","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"in emphasizing the horror of chemical weapons .","depth":9},{"id":132,"text":"`` The question now is what the United States of America and the international community is prepared to do about it ,","depth":8},{"id":133,"text":"because what happened to those people","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"-- to those children --","depth":11},{"id":135,"text":"is not only a violation of international law ,","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"it 's also a danger to our security , ''","depth":9},{"id":137,"text":"Obama added .","depth":7},{"id":138,"text":"Directly addressing questions","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"he received from members of Congress and letters from the public ,","depth":11},{"id":140,"text":"the president insisted","depth":11},{"id":141,"text":"that any U.S. military strike would be limited in scope and mission .","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"`` I know","depth":12},{"id":143,"text":"that after the terrible toll of Iraq and Afghanistan , the idea of any military action","depth":14},{"id":144,"text":"-- no matter how limited --","depth":14},{"id":145,"text":"is not going to be popular , ''","depth":13},{"id":146,"text":"he said ,","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"later declaring :","depth":11},{"id":148,"text":"`` I will not put American boots on the ground in Syria .","depth":12},{"id":149,"text":"I will not pursue an open-ended action like Iraq or Afghanistan .","depth":13},{"id":150,"text":"I will not pursue a prolonged air campaign like Libya or Kosovo .","depth":13},{"id":151,"text":"This would be a targeted strike","depth":9},{"id":152,"text":"to achieve a clear objective ,","depth":10},{"id":153,"text":"deterring the use of chemical weapons","depth":11},{"id":154,"text":"and degrading Assad 's capabilities . ''","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"At the same time , he rejected criticism","depth":9},{"id":156,"text":"that such a limited military response would prove meaningless ,","depth":9},{"id":157,"text":"saying","depth":10},{"id":158,"text":"`` the United States military does n't do pin pricks . ''","depth":10},{"id":159,"text":"`` Even a limited strike will send a message to Assad","depth":12},{"id":160,"text":"that no other nation can deliver , ''","depth":12},{"id":161,"text":"Obama said .","depth":11},{"id":162,"text":"`` I do n't think","depth":12},{"id":163,"text":"we should remove another dictator with force .","depth":12},{"id":164,"text":"We learned from Iraq","depth":13},{"id":165,"text":"that doing so makes us responsible for all","depth":14},{"id":166,"text":"that comes next .","depth":14},{"id":167,"text":"But a targeted strike can makes Assad","depth":14},{"id":168,"text":"-- or any other dictator --","depth":14},{"id":169,"text":"think twice","depth":14},{"id":170,"text":"before using chemical weapons . ''","depth":14},{"id":171,"text":"He described the U.S. role in the world as `` doing more than forging international agreements ;","depth":12},{"id":172,"text":"it has meant enforcing them . ''","depth":12},{"id":173,"text":"`` The burdens of leadership are often heavy ,","depth":13},{"id":174,"text":"but the world 's a better place","depth":14},{"id":175,"text":"because we have borne them , ''","depth":14},{"id":176,"text":"Obama said","depth":12},{"id":177,"text":"before making a direct appeal to both sides of the political spectrum .","depth":11},{"id":178,"text":"`` To my friends on the right , I ask you to reconcile your commitment to America 's military might with the failure","depth":15},{"id":179,"text":"to act","depth":15},{"id":180,"text":"when a cause is so plainly just , ''","depth":14},{"id":181,"text":"he said .","depth":13},{"id":182,"text":"`` To my friends on the left , I ask you to reconcile your belief in freedom and dignity for all people with those images of children","depth":14},{"id":183,"text":"writhing in pain","depth":15},{"id":184,"text":"and going still on a cold hospital floor ,","depth":15},{"id":185,"text":"for sometimes resolutions and statements of condemnation are simply not enough . ''","depth":13},{"id":186,"text":"He concluded","depth":11},{"id":187,"text":"by challenging `` every member of Congress and those of you","depth":14},{"id":188,"text":"watching at home tonight","depth":14},{"id":189,"text":"to view those videos of the attack ,","depth":13},{"id":190,"text":"and then ask","depth":13},{"id":191,"text":"what kind of world will we live in","depth":15},{"id":192,"text":"if the United States of America sees a dictator brazenly violate international law with poison gas","depth":15},{"id":193,"text":"and we choose to look the other way ? ''","depth":14},{"id":194,"text":"McCain and fellow GOP Sen. Lindsey Graham of South Carolina responded","depth":12},{"id":195,"text":"by saying","depth":13},{"id":196,"text":"Obama failed to speak forcefully enough `` about the need","depth":14},{"id":197,"text":"to increase our military assistance to moderate opposition forces in Syria , such as the Free Syrian Army . ''","depth":14},{"id":198,"text":"They called for the United States and its allies on the U.N. Security Council to `` immediately '' offer a resolution ``","depth":14},{"id":199,"text":"that lays out what steps Syria would have to take","depth":16},{"id":200,"text":"to give up its chemical weapons ,","depth":16},{"id":201,"text":"including making a full and accurate declaration of all of its chemical weapons","depth":16},{"id":202,"text":"and granting international monitors unfettered access to all sites in Syria","depth":17},{"id":203,"text":"that possess these weapons . ''","depth":17},{"id":204,"text":"`` This resolution would have to threaten serious consequences","depth":15},{"id":205,"text":"if the Assad regime does not comply , ''","depth":15},{"id":206,"text":"they said ,","depth":14},{"id":207,"text":"calling for an up-or-down vote by the Security Council ,","depth":13},{"id":208,"text":"where Syrian allies Russia and China have so far blocked any U.N. action against Syria .","depth":13},{"id":209,"text":"Rep. Elijah Cummings , a Maryland Democrat and staunch Obama supporter","depth":12},{"id":210,"text":"who is undecided on Syria ,","depth":12},{"id":211,"text":"praised him for `` a very good job ''","depth":11},{"id":212,"text":"but said","depth":11},{"id":213,"text":"his position on the issue remained unchanged .","depth":11},{"id":214,"text":"`` It was not a wasted speech , ''","depth":12},{"id":215,"text":"said Cummings ,","depth":12},{"id":216,"text":"noting","depth":12},{"id":217,"text":"his constituents are tired of war .","depth":12},{"id":218,"text":"`` I thought","depth":11},{"id":219,"text":"he made a great moral argument . ''","depth":11},{"id":220,"text":"For two years , Obama resisted calls by conservative hawks such McCain to back rebels","depth":13},{"id":221,"text":"fighting the al-Assad regime ,","depth":13},{"id":222,"text":"saying","depth":13},{"id":223,"text":"the United States sought no role in the Syrian civil war .","depth":13},{"id":224,"text":"When evidence of chemical weapons use emerged earlier this year ,","depth":13},{"id":225,"text":"and Hezbollah fighters from Lebanon helped al-Assad 's forces gain the upper hand ,","depth":13},{"id":226,"text":"Obama agreed in June to provide military aid to the rebels .","depth":12},{"id":227,"text":"The August attack clearly crossed a `` red line ''","depth":13},{"id":228,"text":"he declared earlier","depth":13},{"id":229,"text":"against chemical weapons use ,","depth":12},{"id":230,"text":"prompting his decision for what he hoped","depth":12},{"id":231,"text":"would be an international military response against Syria .","depth":12},{"id":232,"text":"However , Britain 's Parliament voted against joining a military response ,","depth":12},{"id":233,"text":"denying Obama a normally reliable ally .","depth":12},{"id":234,"text":"He then decided to seek authorization from Congress","depth":12},{"id":235,"text":"to provide political cover","depth":13},{"id":236,"text":"and buy time","depth":14},{"id":237,"text":"to build a broader international coalition .","depth":14},{"id":238,"text":"Now legislators from both parties are threatening to oppose a resolution","depth":12},{"id":239,"text":"authorizing a military response ,","depth":12},{"id":240,"text":"and Obama has asked for time","depth":12},{"id":241,"text":"to let the diplomatic process play out .","depth":12},{"id":242,"text":"Kerry heads to Geneva on Thursday for talks with his Russian counterpart ,","depth":11},{"id":243,"text":"who first offered his government 's proposal Monday","depth":12},{"id":244,"text":"after Kerry earlier said","depth":13},{"id":245,"text":"Syria 's turning over its chemical weapons was the only way","depth":14},{"id":246,"text":"to avoid a U.S. attack .","depth":14},{"id":247,"text":"Syria agreed Tuesday to the Russian proposal ,","depth":12},{"id":248,"text":"with Foreign Minister Walid Moallem saying","depth":13},{"id":249,"text":"his government was ready to disclose the location of its chemical weapons , halt production , and show its facilities to representatives of Russia , the United Nations , and other unspecified states .","depth":13},{"id":250,"text":"At the same time , Russian President Vladimir Putin said Tuesday","depth":12},{"id":251,"text":"that `` all of this will only mean anything","depth":14},{"id":252,"text":"if the United States and other nations","depth":17},{"id":253,"text":"supporting it","depth":17},{"id":254,"text":"tell us","depth":16},{"id":255,"text":"that they 're giving up their plan","depth":16},{"id":256,"text":"to use force against Syria . ''","depth":16},{"id":257,"text":"`` You ca n't really ask Syria , or any other country , to disarm unilaterally","depth":15},{"id":258,"text":"while military action against it is being contemplated , ''","depth":15},{"id":259,"text":"Putin said in an interview with a Russian television network .","depth":14},{"id":260,"text":"For his part , Obama sought to persuade Americans of the opposite","depth":10},{"id":261,"text":"-- that the diplomatic stirrings by Russia and Syria occurred","depth":11},{"id":262,"text":"because of the credible threat of a military attack","depth":12},{"id":263,"text":"intended to deter Syria from using its chemical weapons again .","depth":12},{"id":264,"text":"The president has not said","depth":8},{"id":265,"text":"whether he would launch strikes","depth":9},{"id":266,"text":"without the support of Congress .","depth":9},{"id":267,"text":"Meanwhile , a bipartisan group of eight senators is working on an alternative resolution to the one","depth":10},{"id":268,"text":"authorizing military action","depth":11},{"id":269,"text":"already passed by the Senate Foreign Relations Committee .","depth":11},{"id":270,"text":"It would include `` guidelines , reporting process and benchmarks","depth":11},{"id":271,"text":"that have to be met , ''","depth":11},{"id":272,"text":"McCain told CNN .","depth":10},{"id":273,"text":"On the House side , Democratic Rep. Chris Van Hollen of Maryland said","depth":9},{"id":274,"text":"he was working on a version of a resolution","depth":11},{"id":275,"text":"that would authorize a military response","depth":11},{"id":276,"text":"if the diplomatic process failed to yield an acceptable result in 30 days .","depth":10},{"id":277,"text":"The Obama administration has launched a sweeping lobbying effort ,","depth":8},{"id":278,"text":"with the president meeting on Capitol Hill on Tuesday with senators from both parties as part of a series of classified briefings , hearings and other consultations on the Syria issue .","depth":8},{"id":279,"text":"Since Friday , the administration has spoken with at least 93 senators and more than 350 members of the House ,","depth":9},{"id":280,"text":"a White House official said Tuesday .","depth":9},{"id":281,"text":"Despite such outreach ,","depth":11},{"id":282,"text":"indications were that the congressional push was n't working .","depth":11},{"id":283,"text":"Sen. Mitch McConnell , the top-ranking Republican in the Senate , announced Tuesday","depth":12},{"id":284,"text":"he will vote against authorizing military action on Syria .","depth":12},{"id":285,"text":"So did Democratic Sen. Ed Markey of Massachusetts ,","depth":12},{"id":286,"text":"who won the seat","depth":13},{"id":287,"text":"vacated by Kerry","depth":14},{"id":288,"text":"when he became secretary of state .","depth":14},{"id":289,"text":"A running CNN vote count showed","depth":10},{"id":290,"text":"most members of Congress remained undecided , with significant opposition in both chambers among the much smaller numbers","depth":11},{"id":291,"text":"who have announced their decision","depth":12},{"id":292,"text":"leaving the outcome in doubt .","depth":12}],"relations":[{"parent":585,"left":298,"right":584,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":298,"left":295,"right":297,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":295,"left":294,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":294,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":297,"left":3,"right":296,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":296,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":584,"left":325,"right":583,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":325,"left":317,"right":324,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":317,"left":304,"right":316,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":304,"left":301,"right":303,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":301,"left":299,"right":300,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":299,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":300,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":303,"left":10,"right":302,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":302,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":316,"left":308,"right":315,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":308,"left":13,"right":307,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":307,"left":305,"right":306,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":305,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":306,"left":16,"right":17,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":315,"left":311,"right":314,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":311,"left":310,"right":21,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":310,"left":18,"right":309,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":309,"left":19,"right":20,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":314,"left":22,"right":313,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":313,"left":23,"right":312,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":312,"left":24,"right":25,"relati